                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The text was copied in a <term type="script">mixed minuscule
                                        bouletée</term> script, slanting slightly to the left, in
                                    brown ink, with modest variation in letter size.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations are not used apart from the horizontal
                                    stroke for <hi rend="italic">nu</hi>, and this appears only at
                                    the end of lines, as do superscript word endings. Breathings are
                                    angular and mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent. There is
                                    occasional decorative use of the double dot, and when this
                                    appears on the first letter of a word, the breathing may be
                                    omitted. <foreign xml:lang="la">Nomina sacra</foreign> are
                                    unaccentuated. <foreign xml:lang="la">Nomina sacra</foreign>
                                    strokes are decorated with X-shapes.</p>
                                <p>Majuscule letter forms in use include <hi rend="italic">delta</hi>, <hi rend="italic">epsilon</hi>, <hi rend="italic">zeta</hi>, <hi rend="italic">eta</hi>, <hi rend="italic">kappa</hi>, <hi rend="italic">lambda</hi>, <hi rend="italic">sigma</hi> and <hi rend="italic">psi</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the lower, middle and upper points
                                    and full stop.</p>
                                <p>Headings for chapters and the names of authors were written by
                                    the same hand in <term type="script">Alexandrine</term>
                                    majuscule script.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

